Claims CLAIMS: 1. A method of controlling a drilling choke in a drilling system, the method comprising: monitoring a parameter in the drilling system; monitoring position of the drilling choke; determining an adjustment to the position of the drilling choke based on the monitored parameter and the monitored position; producing an actuation of an actuator operably coupled to the drilling choke to implement the adjustment; transferring, with a transfer mechanism, the actuation of the actuator to motion of the drilling choke in a non-linear relationship; and altering the monitored parameter in response to the implemented adjustment of the drilling choke. 2. The method of claim 1, wherein monitoring the parameter in the controlled pressure system comprises monitoring the parameter including flow-in, flow-out, density, and standpipe pressure. 3. The method of claim 1 or 2, wherein monitoring the position of the drilling choke comprises obtaining an indication of the position from a position sensor operably connected to the drilling choke. 4. The method of claim 1, 2 or 3, wherein determining the adjustment to the position of the drilling choke based on the monitored parameter and the monitored position comprises correlating a change from the monitored position to a new position of the drilling choke relative to a change from a current value the monitored parameter to a new value for the monitored parameter. 5. The method of any one of claims 1 to 4, wherein producing the actuation of the actuator operably coupled to the drilling choke to implement the adjustment comprises operating a hydraulic motor with a hydraulic power unit. 6. The method of any one of claims 1 to 4, wherein producing the actuation of the actuator operably coupled to the drilling choke to implement the adjustment comprises operating an electric motor with a power supply. 7. The method of any one of claims 1 to 6, wherein transferring, with the transfer mechanism, the actuation of the actuator to the motion of the drilling choke in the non- 

 linear relationship comprises transferring, with the transfer mechanism, the actuation to the motion in the non-linear relationship relative to the position of the drilling choke. 8. The method of claim 7, wherein transferring, with the transfer mechanism, the actuation to the motion in the non-linear relationship relative to the position of the drilling choke comprises making the motion quicker when near the position of being fully opened and making the motion slower when near the position of being fully closed. 9. The method of claim 7 or 8, wherein transferring, with the transfer mechanism, the actuation to the motion in the non-linear relationship relative to the position of the drilling choke comprises making the motion greater when near the position of being fully opened and making the motion smaller when near the position of being fully closed. 10. The method of any one of claims 1 to 9, wherein transferring with the transfer mechanism comprises transferring with the transfer mechanism operable between the actuator and the drilling choke. 11. The method of claim 10, wherein the transfer mechanism comprises at least one of: a linkage operable between the actuator and the drilling choke; a crank and slider linkage operable between the actuator and the drilling choke; a bell crank linkage operable between the actuator and the drilling choke; a gear arrangement operable between the actuator and the drilling choke; a chain and sprockets operable between the actuator and the drilling choke; and a variable transmission operable between the actuator and the drilling choke. 12. The method of any one of claims 1 to 9, wherein transferring with the transfer mechanism comprises transferring with the transfer mechanism operable between a power source and the actuator. 13. The method of claim 12, wherein the transfer mechanism comprises at least one of: a throttling valve operable between a hydraulic source of the power source and a hydraulic motor of the actuator; a throttling valve operable between a hydraulic source of the power source and a hydraulic motor of the actuator and having a stem directly operated by movement of the valve; a drive operable between an electric source of the power source and an electric motor of the actuator; a control valve operable between a hydraulic source of the power source and a variable speed motor of the actuator; and at least one control algorithm being operable to control the actuator. 14. The method of any one of claims 1 to 13, wherein altering the monitored parameter in response to the implemented adjustment of the drilling choke comprises changing surface backpressure of the controlled pressure system. 15. A programmable storage device having program instructions stored thereon for causing a programmable control device to perform a method according to of any one of claims 1 to 14. 16. A method of controlling a choke, the method comprising: monitoring position of the choke; receiving an adjustment to the position of the choke; producing an actuation of an actuator operably coupled to the choke to implement the received adjustment; transferring the actuation of the actuator with a transfer mechanism to motion of the choke in a non-linear relationship; and altering the position of the choke in response to the implemented adjustment. 17. An apparatus for a pressure system, the apparatus comprising: a valve in operable communication with the pressure system; a position sensor in operable communication with the valve and obtaining position of the valve; an actuator in operable communication with the valve; a controller in operable communication with the position sensor and the actuator, the controller receiving an adjustment to the position of the valve and producing an actuation of the actuator to implement the received adjustment; and a transfer mechanism transferring the actuation of the actuator to motion of the valve in a non-linear relationship. 18. The apparatus of claim 17, wherein the valve is selected from the group consisting of a choke, a needle valve, a ball valve, a gate valve, a globe valve, a plug valve, a disc choke with plates, and a butterfly valve. 19. The apparatus of claim 17, wherein the valve comprises a drilling choke in fluid communication with a borehole; and wherein the controller is operable to: monitor a parameter in the pressure system; monitor the position of the drilling choke; 

 determine the adjustment to the position of the drilling choke based on the monitored parameter and the monitored position; and produce the actuation of the actuator operably coupled to the drilling choke to implement the adjustment. 20. The apparatus of claim 17, 18 or 19, wherein the transfer mechanism is operable between the actuator and the valve and comprises at least one of: a linkage operable between the actuator and the valve; a crank and slider linkage operable between the actuator and the valve; a bell crank linkage operable between the actuator and the valve; Î¯ gear arrangement operable between the actuator and the valve; a chain and sprockets operable between the actuator and the valve; and a variable transmission operable between the actuator and the valve. 21. The apparatus of claim 17, 18 or 19, wherein the transfer mechanism is operable between a power source and the actuator and comprises at least one of: a throttling valve operable between a hydraulic source of the power source and a hydraulic motor of the actuator; a throttling valve operable between a hydraulic source of the power source and hydraulic motor of the actuator and having a stem directly operated by movement of the valve; a drive operable between an electric source of the power source and an electric motor of the actuator; a control valve operable between a hydraulic source of the power source and a variable speed motor of the actuator; and at least one control algorithm bein operable to control the actuator.
